an grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight."},{"version":"black-2","text":"As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if it\u2019s torn apart."},{"version":"white-2","text":"As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if it\u2019s torn apart."},{"version":"x","text":"Even if its body is torn, it can regenerate as long as the glowing central core remains intact."},{"version":"y","text":"It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Staryu\u2019s center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pok\u00e9mon look like the stars in the sky."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Staryu apparently communicates with the stars in the night sky by flashing the red core at the center of its body. If parts of its body are torn, this Pok\u00e9mon simply regenerates the missing pieces and limbs."},{"version":"sun","text":"Large numbers of these Pok\u00e9mon make their home at the seaside. At night, a strange red glow radiates from the center of their bodies."},{"version":"moon","text":"This Pok\u00e9mon gets nibbled on by Lumineon and others. Thanks to its red core, it regenerates fast, so it\u2019s unconcerned by their snack attacks."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"In many places, there are folktales of stardust falling into the ocean and becoming Staryu."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"No number of injuries can bother Staryu. Its amazing regenerative powers return it to its previous state in half a day!"},{"version":"lets-go-pikachu","text":"As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pok\u00e9mon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits."},{"version":"lets-go-eevee","text":"As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pok\u00e9mon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits."},{"version":"sw